nib.text:
A man was shot in Willard-Hay on Sunday morning, officials stated.

Police responded to a ShotSpotter activation, which is a technology that uses microphones to scan for the unique acoustic signature of gunfire, on the 2700 block of Upton Avenue North around 5 a.m.

When officers arrived, they found a man inside a vehicle suffering from a gunshot wound.

Medics transported the man to an area hospital. He is expected to recover.

Police are investigating the shooting. No arrests have been made.

nib.text:
A four-unit apartment building in Sumner-Glenwood was extensively damaged in a fire early Sunday morning, firefighters say. 

At 3 a.m. firefighters responded to a report of a building fire. 

Upon arrival, they observed fire on the second floor, third floor, and roof of the three-story apartment building. All of the building's residents had already safely evacuated.

Citizen user videos showed massive flames shooting from the residence. 

After discovering the roof was compromised due to the blaze, firefighters were asked to evacuate the building and a second alarm was called to request additional personnel and equipment to the scene. 

Minneapolis Fire officials detailed the response on Twitter, which included shutting off the gas and spraying the exterior of the building with at least four streams of water. 

By 4:37 a.m., the fire was deemed under control. 

An image shared by firefighters shows portions of the building, including the roof, were destroyed by the blaze.

No injuries were reported by firefighters or residents and the cause of the fire is under investigation.
